Yesterday was the one year of my mother being rushed to the hospital. I want to post thoughts because I know a lot of others are going through it as well.
There isn’t certain days/moments etc that remind me of her more than her “I love you” texts every night or FaceTimes worry what her son is up to up to now to
Stress her out 😊. 

It’s been an adjustment sometimes going days without anyone checking in . My friends have yes but there is nothing that will compare to your Mom. Not having that is hitting hard the most. I’m saying this because I’ve realized over the past year that it’s hard to talk to people Because when you say you’re having a hard time/bad day they go straight to the absolute worst thought like we need help.. If someone does be vulnerable and open up just know we are grieving at our own speed and we just sometimes need an ear to vent to. I’ve had like most some dark days ( a lot). We judge ourselves enough about what we could’ve done better or differently but slowly I’m learning to be more empathetic with myself knowing that this process will never make any sense. 

Just don’t say to yourself you shouldn’t feel this or a certain way. Allow yourself to feel these emotions because it will help you grieve. 
Do me a favor and go see your parents more frequently than just the holidays. Family is everything ❤️
